      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Unfixed, but low priority-- why would a miner create a block that is likely to get orphaned because it takes peers so long to validate?  And even if they did, and the block was not orphaned, all they accomplish is making full-chain catch-up validation take longer for a while (until a new release with a new checkpoint, because we skip signature checking up to the last checkpoint).\n",
